## Additional Recommended Parameters

Users may extend `99-custom.conf` depending on workload.

### Memory & Performance

```conf
vm.dirty_ratio = 15
vm.dirty_background_ratio = 5
vm.overcommit_memory = 1
```

* `dirty_ratio`: Max percentage of dirty pages before writeback
* `dirty_background_ratio`: Background flush threshold
* `overcommit_memory=1`: Allows flexible memory allocation (useful for builds)

---

### Security Hardening

```conf
kernel.kptr_restrict = 2
kernel.dmesg_restrict = 1
kernel.randomize_va_space = 2
kernel.unprivileged_bpf_disabled = 1
```

* Restricts kernel pointer exposure
* Limits `dmesg` access
* Enables full ASLR
* Disables unprivileged BPF (reduces attack surface)

---

### Networking (Optional Hardening)

```conf
net.ipv4.tcp_syncookies = 1
net.ipv4.conf.all.rp_filter = 1
net.ipv4.icmp_echo_ignore_broadcasts = 1
```

---

## Customization Guidelines

Users should adjust values based on:

| Scenario              | Recommended Changes              |
| --------------------- | -------------------------------- |
| Low RAM (<4GB)        | Increase `swappiness` (20–40)    |
| High RAM (16GB+)      | Keep `swappiness` low (5–10)     |
| Server workloads      | Increase cache pressure (75–100) |
| Desktop/dev workloads | Lower cache pressure (30–50)     |

